text: Galbraith is an unincorporated community in Kossuth County, in the U.S. state of Iowa. ==History== A post office was established at Galbraith in 1902, and remained in operation until it was discontinued in 1913. The community was named for an Iowa senator named Galbraith. ==References== Category:Unincorporated communities in Kossuth County, Iowa Category:1902 establishments in Iowa Category:Populated places established in 1902 Category:Unincorporated communities in Iowa
